1
00:01:00,399 --> 00:01:01,159
Did uncle leave?

2
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:02,119
Yes.

3
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,680
He kept reminding me

4
00:01:04,879 --> 00:01:05,959
to be careful.

5
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:09,280
Your dad wants to steal my dad's girlfriend.

6
00:01:09,359 --> 00:01:10,359
And you just agreed?

7
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,319
Your dad's girlfriend

8
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:14,000
was my dad's wife for ten years.

9
00:01:16,439 --> 00:01:16,840
But

10
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:18,560
they got divorced.

11
00:01:19,319 --> 00:01:20,519
They broke up.

12
00:01:20,719 --> 00:01:22,760
The best thing to do with an ex is to disappear.

13
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:33,359
Is that so?

14
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:43,680
You haven't disappeared either.

15
00:01:53,879 --> 00:01:54,760
Lan Xiaochuan!

16
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,640
Lan Xiaochuan!

17
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:58,439
Xiaochuan!

18
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:00,680
Who's there?

19
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:01,760
Lan Xiaochuan!

20
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,040
It's fine.

21
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,439
Wait for me.

22
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,240
I told you not to come to the clinic.

23
00:02:13,879 --> 00:02:14,599
Xiaochuan!

24
00:02:15,919 --> 00:02:17,680
How many years have you not seen me?

25
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:20,280
You don't care about me anymore,

26
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:21,199
do you?

27
00:02:21,719 --> 00:02:23,280
Give me 8,000 yuan today.

28
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,840
If you give me one cent less,

29
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:27,680
I'll spend the night at your mother's grave.

30
00:02:29,319 --> 00:02:30,439
Last month, 5,000 yuan.

31
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:31,759
Today, 8,000 yuan.

32
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,520
Are you taking advantage of me?

33
00:02:33,919 --> 00:02:34,960
Get out of my clinic.

34
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,199
Don't dirty my clinic.

35
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,199
Fine.

36
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,719
You are a loser.

37
00:02:39,879 --> 00:02:42,120
Your mom left you

38
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:44,439
for me to raise.

39
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,919
Now that you've grown up,

40
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,240
you've forgotten your roots.

41
00:02:48,039 --> 00:02:49,400
I'm a burden? What are you?

42
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,560
I never spent a penny of your money.

43
00:02:53,639 --> 00:02:55,039
You can't even support yourself.

44
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:57,400
Bull... bullshit!

45
00:02:58,319 --> 00:03:00,800
Now you're all dressed up

46
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,800
in your white coat,

47
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,560
acting like you're someone important.

48
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:05,840
Fine,

49
00:03:06,439 --> 00:03:07,199
Today,

50
00:03:07,879 --> 00:03:10,240
I'll tear your skin off!

51
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,439
You...

52
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,919
Ouch, ouch, ouch!

53
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:18,360
Xiaochuan,

54
00:03:18,639 --> 00:03:20,719
where did you find this wild man?

55
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,360
Shut up!

56
00:03:23,639 --> 00:03:25,240
Why does he look so familiar?

57
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,080
I'm telling you...

58
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:30,520
Look again,

59
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,960
and I'll rip your eyes out!

60
00:03:35,159 --> 00:03:36,479
You ungrateful wretch!

61
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,400
Just you wait!

62
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,840
I'll go to your father tomorrow!

63
00:03:39,159 --> 00:03:40,080
Just you wait!

64
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,080
You ungrateful wretch!

65
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:50,199
Are you okay?

66
00:03:53,439 --> 00:03:54,360
He's your uncle?

67
00:03:55,639 --> 00:03:57,080
Why haven't you ever mentioned him?

68
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,919
It's not your business.

69
00:04:02,479 --> 00:04:03,360
Why should I tell you?

70
00:04:04,159 --> 00:04:05,039
If he's giving you trouble,

71
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,560
tell me where he lives.

72
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:07,520
I'll go deal with him.

73
00:04:08,319 --> 00:04:09,840
Leave when you're done watching the drama.

74
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,879
I told you it's none of your business.

75
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:13,960
Your family's issues

76
00:04:15,719 --> 00:04:17,040
will be my family's issues in the future.

77
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,639
Just leave. I want to be alone.

78
00:04:29,879 --> 00:04:30,439
Fine.

79
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,439
Don't forget I have your dirt.

80
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,240
Transfer the money by 10 AM tomorrow.

81
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:57,959
Xiaochuan,

82
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,560
I'm your uncle.

83
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:03,279
I won't push you into a corner.

84
00:05:03,399 --> 00:05:05,000
Do as I say.

85
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:05,800
Don't be stubborn.

86
00:05:05,959 --> 00:05:07,240
If something goes wrong,

87
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,480
your century-old clinic

88
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:10,920
will be closed.

89
00:05:11,319 --> 00:05:11,720
By the way,

90
00:05:13,759 --> 00:05:16,279
you have a boyfriend, right?

91
00:05:16,519 --> 00:05:18,560
He has a decent job, doesn't he?

92
00:05:18,759 --> 00:05:20,199
If something goes wrong,

93
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:22,560
it will also affect his future.

94
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:23,720
Think about it.

95
00:06:15,759 --> 00:06:16,639
I didn't expect

96
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,519
Yunfei to come to check the homework.

97
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,959
He's the one who led our model airplane team

98
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,279
to win the national championship.

99
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,800
He looks like Professor Du.

100
00:06:22,959 --> 00:06:24,040
He has a better face than Professor Du.

101
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:25,399
He is Professor Du's son.

102
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,199
Of course, he's good-looking.

103
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,759
I wonder if he has a girlfriend.

104
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,879
Whose model is this?

105
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,439
Mine.

106
00:06:32,879 --> 00:06:33,600
There are a few coefficients

107
00:06:43,519 --> 00:06:44,839
that are calculated incorrectly in your drawings.

108
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,240
Go back and calculate it again.

109
00:06:47,399 --> 00:06:48,839
There are better materials available.

110
00:06:49,519 --> 00:06:50,480
Try a few more times.

111
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:51,040
Okay.

112
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:52,759
Thank you, Mr. Lu.

113
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,040
I'll treat you to coffee later.

114
00:06:56,279 --> 00:06:56,920
Alright.

115
00:06:57,319 --> 00:06:58,439
It's time for lunch.

116
00:06:58,639 --> 00:06:59,759
Everyone, go have lunch.

117
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,959
We'll discuss any issues in this afternoon's class.

118
00:07:02,279 --> 00:07:02,759
Okay.

119
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,160
Goodbye, professor.

120
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,319
Goodbye, professor.

121
00:07:06,439 --> 00:07:07,399
- Goodbye, sir. - Goodbye, Professor Du.

122
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:08,399
Goodbye, sir.

123
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,759
I shouldn't have brought you here.

124
00:07:14,879 --> 00:07:15,480
Now that you're here,

125
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,720
these young girls in the class

126
00:07:16,839 --> 00:07:18,279
are not focusing on their studies anymore.

127
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,439
What does this have to do with me?

128
00:07:20,399 --> 00:07:21,319
What do you think?

129
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:24,279
You really didn't learn from me.

130
00:07:24,439 --> 00:07:26,040
You have a pretty face,

131
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,839
but you're not smart.

132
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:31,199
Being not smart doesn't stop me from leading a championship team.

133
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,920
You're really like your dad.

134
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,199
You're like a block of wood.

135
00:07:37,439 --> 00:07:37,879
When will you find a girlfriend

136
00:07:37,879 --> 00:07:39,319
if you're like this?

137
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:43,480
Mom,

138
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,839
have you been in touch with my dad recently?

139
00:07:46,079 --> 00:07:46,680
No.

140
00:07:48,199 --> 00:07:49,680
When are you going to tell my dad

141
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,000
about Uncle Lan?

142
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:53,879
What should I tell him?

143
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,680
Just tell him when the time comes.

144
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:56,920
By the way,

145
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,720
when you come back from your vacation,

146
00:07:58,879 --> 00:08:00,480
help me keep an eye on the model airplane team.

147
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,560
I have an appointment at noon. I'm leaving.

148
00:08:02,759 --> 00:08:03,439
What appointment?

149
00:08:03,959 --> 00:08:05,079
Seeing a traditional Chinese doctor.

150
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:23,680
Dujuan.

151
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:24,680
Professor Du.

152
00:08:26,519 --> 00:08:27,000
Dad.

153
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,000
Why are you here?

154
00:08:29,959 --> 00:08:30,879
Why are you here?

155
00:08:39,399 --> 00:08:41,159
I just attended a forum.

156
00:08:41,279 --> 00:08:42,720
So I'm dressed a bit more formally.

157
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:45,399
You know the flowers

158
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,639
are from someone else.

159
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:47,360
Got it?

160
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:48,480
Got it.

161
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:50,840
Where's your mom?

162
00:08:56,039 --> 00:08:57,519
My mom...

163
00:08:59,039 --> 00:08:59,639
Senior

164
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,039
Coffee.

165
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,639
Where did Professor Du go?

166
00:09:05,799 --> 00:09:07,080
I just saw her.

167
00:09:07,519 --> 00:09:09,879
She said she was going to the hospital.

168
00:09:10,039 --> 00:09:10,679
Hospital?

169
00:09:11,879 --> 00:09:12,559
Your mom is sick?

170
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,120
You little rascal,

171
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,519
why didn't you tell me?

172
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:17,000
Which hospital did she go to?

173
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,320
That one,

174
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:23,399
Hua Shan Hospital.

175
00:09:23,639 --> 00:09:24,879
No, I know,

176
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,120
it's called Shengxiu Hall.

177
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,240
Look at you,

178
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,600
how are you taking care of your mom?

179
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,200
You don't even know which hospital she went to.

180
00:09:31,399 --> 00:09:32,320
I'll go check on her right away.

181
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,080
Dad, Dad, Dad.

182
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:33,720
Take it easy, Dad.

183
00:09:33,919 --> 00:09:34,360
Dad.

184
00:09:34,639 --> 00:09:35,320
Senior,

185
00:09:35,919 --> 00:09:36,879
your coffee.

186
00:09:44,159 --> 00:09:45,240
Juan, look.

187
00:09:46,679 --> 00:09:47,159
You

188
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:48,759
have weak blood and energy.

189
00:09:49,399 --> 00:09:52,039
I made you ginseng chicken soup

190
00:09:52,159 --> 00:09:53,360
to boost your blood and energy.

191
00:09:53,519 --> 00:09:55,000
Ginseng chicken soup?

192
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,080
What's this then?

193
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:58,200
Why don't I have a single slice of ginseng?

194
00:09:58,279 --> 00:10:00,159
Sweetie, with your fiery temper,

195
00:10:00,279 --> 00:10:02,000
if you drink ginseng soup, you'll be too energetic.

196
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,720
Young people should eat some mung bean porridge.

197
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,240
Look, mung bean porridge.

198
00:10:07,519 --> 00:10:08,559
You old man,

199
00:10:08,759 --> 00:10:10,360
you have double standards.

200
00:10:21,679 --> 00:10:22,919
My dad will be at the hospital soon.

201
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:23,679
Cooperate with him.

202
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:26,559
Try it.

203
00:10:26,879 --> 00:10:27,519
Thank you.

204
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,360
Is it good?

205
00:10:42,639 --> 00:10:43,039
I'm so sorry.

206
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:43,919
-Are you okay? -I'm sorry.

207
00:10:44,039 --> 00:10:44,720
Are you okay?

208
00:10:44,879 --> 00:10:45,440
Are you okay, Dad?

209
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:47,399
He must have burned himself, ma'am.

210
00:10:47,559 --> 00:10:48,759
There's burn cream

211
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:50,240
in the treatment room.

212
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:51,159
Take my dad there.

213
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:51,759
Okay.

214
00:10:51,919 --> 00:10:52,639
Come on, this way.

215
00:10:52,759 --> 00:10:53,440
Hurry.

216
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,000
This way.

217
00:10:56,159 --> 00:10:56,519
Hurry.

218
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,279
We need to deal with this quickly.

219
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,200
Auntie Du,

220
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,600
please help my dad with this.

221
00:11:00,679 --> 00:11:01,000
Okay.

222
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,519
Dad, it's over there.

223
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:04,600
No, no.

224
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,519
Yes, it's over there.

225
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:08,919
Xiaochuan, it's not appropriate.

226
00:11:08,919 --> 00:11:10,039
I'll do it myself.

227
00:11:10,279 --> 00:11:11,039
It's appropriate.

228
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,360
Very appropriate.

229
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:17,320
Why did he lock the door?

230
00:11:20,399 --> 00:11:20,919
Dad.

231
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:21,559
Well...

232
00:11:23,039 --> 00:11:23,759
Xiaochuan.

233
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:26,519
No wonder this place looks familiar.

234
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,200
Your girlfriend is a good doctor.

235
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:28,919
Let her

236
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,720
take care of your mom.

237
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:31,639
Okay.

238
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,480
Where's your mom?

239
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:35,639
My mom...

240
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:40,000
Where's my mom?
